FuncDef: The start l2tp delete ip command deletes a locked LNS IP address.

ParaDef.Info:
Specifies a locked LNS IP address to be deleted.
The value is in dotted decimal notation.

ExtraInfo:
Usage Scenario
If the LNS IP address configured using the start l2tp ip ip-address command is incorrect or unavailable, run the block lns-ip command to lock the LNS IP address before deleting it using the start l2tp delete ip command.
Prerequisites
An LNS IP address list has been configured using the start l2tp ip ip-address command.
Priority-based load balancing for tunnels has been configured using the tunnel priority command in the L2TP group view.
The LNS IP address to be deleted has been locked using the block lns-ip lns-ip-address command in the L2TP group view.
The L2TP tunnel to which the LNS IP address to be deleted is bound has been deleted using the reset l2tp tunnel lac remote-address ip-address l2tp-group group-name command.
